President Obama has nominated Justice Morgan Christen for the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit. Justice Christen was born and raised in Washington state and attended the University of Washington, where she received her B.A. in 1983. She later obtained her J.D. from Golden Gate University School of Law in 1986. Justice Christen moved to Alaska in 1986 and began a clerkship for the Honorable Brian Shortell of the Alaska Superior Court. She joined the law firm of Preston Thorgrimson Ellis & Holman (now K&L Gates LLP) in 1987 and became a partner in 1992. In 2001, she was appointed to the Alaska Superior Court and in 2005, she became the presiding judge of Alaska's Third Judicial District. In 2009, she was elevated to serve as one of five Justices on Alaska's Supreme Court. President Obama expressed confidence that Justice Christen will serve the American people with integrity and distinction.